[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[0.069, "o", "A CLI for exploring and managing ServiceNow instances.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.009, "o", "Usage:\r\n  jsn [command]\r\n\r\nAvailable Commands:\r\n  acls            Manage Access Control Lists (ACLs)\r\n  auth            Authentication commands\r\n  choices         Manage choice values\r\n  client-scripts  Manage client scripts\r\n  commands        List all available commands\r\n  compare         Compare resources across instances\r\n  completion      Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell\r\n  config          Configuration management\r\n  docs            Access ServiceNow documentation from sn.jace.pro\r\n  export          Export ServiceNow resources\r\n  flows           Manage Flow Designer flows\r\n  forms           Manage UI Forms\r\n  generate        Generate code templates\r\n  help            Help about any command\r\n  import          Import ServiceNow resources\r\n  instance        Instance information and diagnostics\r\n  jobs            Manage scheduled jobs/scripts\r\n  logs            Query system logs\r\n  records         Manage table records\r\n  rules           Manage business rules\r\n  script-includes Manage script includes\r\n  setup           Interactive first-time setup\r\n  sp              Manage Service Portals\r\n  sp-pages        Manage Service Portal Pages\r\n  sp-widgets      Manage Service Portal Widgets\r\n  tables          Manage tables\r\n  ui-policies     Manage UI policies\r\n  ui-scripts      Manage UI Scripts\r\n  updateset       Manage update sets\r\n  version         Show version information\r\n\r\nFlags:\r\n      --agent            Agent mode (JSON + quiet + no interactive prompts)\r\n      --config string    config file (default is $HOME/.config/servicenow/config.json)\r\n  -h, --help             help for jsn\r\n      --jq string        Apply jq filter to JSON output\r\n      --json             Output as JSON\r\n      --md               Output as Markdown\r\n      --no-interactive   Disable interactive prompts (for scripts/CI)\r\n  -p, --profile string   profile to use\r\n  -q, --quiet            Quiet output (data only, no envelope)\r\n\r\nUse \"jsn [command] --help\" for more information about a command.\r\n"]
